article.p:
p can be expressed as a Gibbs

distribution

<span id="MathJax-Element-65-Frame" class="mjx-chtml MathJax_CHTML" tabindex="0" data-mathml="p(x)∝exp⁡{−∑C∈C(G)EC(xC)}” role=”presentation” style=”font-size: 109%; position: relative;”>p(x)∝exp{−∑C∈C(G)EC(xC)}p(x)∝exp⁡{−∑C∈C(G)EC(xC)}

\begin{aligned}

    T^t \ket{p}

    = T^t \sum_{k=0}^{n-1} p_k \ket{\tilde{k}}

    = \sum_{k=0}^{n-1} p_k \lambda_k^t \ket{\tilde k}.\end{aligned}
